54.4	Gordon_Matta-Clark	Gordon Matta-Clark	Gordon Matta-Clark (June 22, 1943 â€“ August 27, 1978) was an American artist best known for his site-specific artworks he made in the 1970s. He is famous for his "building cuts," a series of works in abandoned buildings in which he variously removed sections of floors, ceilings, and walls.	
